@junrao  I just created a new branch based off of the trunk, applied my changes there and created a new PR.  Could you please take a look:
https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/2378

@tcrayford I have created a new PR after the above discussions. It implements 'time-since-last-run-ms' metric we discussed some time back.

As we don't know the type of the value before-hand, accepting a value as numeric type can leads to error.

e.g Consider a ConfigDef requires a short value (replication-factor)
```
Object value = (Integer) 32770;
if (value instanceof Number) {
	System.out.println("Short Value : " + ((Number) value).shortValue()); // returns negative value
}
```
